text: The wharf in 2018 Torpedo Wharf is a wharf in the Presidio of San Francisco, in the U.S. state of California. The site has been a wharf since 1854, and earned its current name when the United States Army built a naval mine depot . The current wharf was established in 1941, and now serves as a popular tourist destination. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Presidio of San Francisco Category:Tourist attractions in San Francisco Category:Wharves in the United States
title: Torpedo Wharf
